			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Why we&rsquo;re different:</strong></p>
<p>
UNIT4 Business Software is a $576 million enterprise resource planning (ERP) company and a top six mid-market ERP software player globally. Our North American headquarters are located in Victoria, B.C., where we work hard to be a top-rated employer &ndash; not to toot our own horn but you may have seen some of our awards from the Victoria Advanced Technology Council (VIATeC) and Camosun College. All these accolades are great but that&rsquo;s not why we strive to be &lsquo;Employer of the Year&rsquo; day in and day out &ndash; we do it because we know our competitive advantage lies in the performance of our staff. Here at UNIT4, we cultivate a challenging yet relaxed work atmosphere, where people get satisfaction from doing great work under equally great working conditions. We respect each other and our customers, and we respect the principles of work/life balance.<br />
<br />
<strong>Here&rsquo;s a taste of some of what UNIT4&rsquo;s Development department handles:</strong><br />
&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>
the development of two major and several minor products within the Agresso product suite;</li>
<li>
the customization of the product suite for specific customers, ranging from very small to enormous multi-year projects; and</li>
<li>
the adaptation of the standard product to U.S. and Canadian requirements.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>What this job is about:</strong>&nbsp;<br />
<br />
The Application Developer is responsible for creating and maintaining software products and/or custom applications using the Agresso product suite. Primary duties include performing the full range of software development and maintenance activities for these products and applications. The methodologies we use vary depending on the type of work, from Agile to more traditional waterfall.<br />
<br />
<strong>Tasks we expect you to perform:</strong><br />
&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>
Write software according to the specified business requirements, following the established coding standards;</li>
<li>
Perform unit testing of all work and document code as per guidelines;</li>
<li>
Write test scripts for Test-Driven Development when required;</li>
<li>
Review user requirements to create designs and/or review design specifications to create technical specifications;</li>
<li>
Triage reported software defects, debug issues, isolate issues, and fix or identify appropriate workarounds or necessary design changes;</li>
<li>
Performance tune specific functions when necessary;</li>
<li>
Deliver a high level of value and satisfaction to both external and internal customers. This means being customer-focused, producing high-quality work, having a can-do attitude and being both positive and respectful with others.</li>
</ul>
<p>
Skills and assets we expect you to have:<br />
&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>
A degree or diploma providing a strong foundation of practical software development/engineering knowledge, with emphasis on business applications;</li>
<li>
At least two years of relevant software development experience working on business applications running on top of relational database systems;</li>
<li>
Core technical skills required are: C#, SQL, and Visual Studio;</li>
<li>
Desirable technical skills are: C++, MS SQL Server, Oracle TSQL, and Microsoft Team Foundation Server;</li>
<li>
Additional nice to have skills are: WCF/Web Services, ASP.NET, XML, HTML, JavaScript, CSS, MVC, SharePoint development;</li>
<li>
Experience with TDD, Agile and/or structured SDLC processes are definite assets;</li>
<li>
Ability to learn quickly and be self-taught;</li>
<li>
Capacity to research and identify solutions independently, but seek help when appropriate;</li>
<li>
Strong verbal and written English communication skills;</li>
<li>
Familiarity with business processes in a variety of sectors, in particular Finance/Accounting, Logistics, Human Resources, Payroll, Student Information Systems or Project Management;</li>
<li>
Big bonus points for prior experience with and an aptitude for direct customer interaction, in either requirements analysis or support/trouble-shooting.<br />
&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>The lay of the land</strong></p>
<p>
The Software Developer reports to the Development Manager. He or she works out of the Victoria, B.C. office, has no direct reports and has minimal travel requirements.<br />
<br />
<strong>Join us in &ldquo;embracing change&rdquo;</strong><br />
<br />
Around the world, we look for potential employees who are confident team players and have an unswerving commitment to excellence in customer service to help us in our mission to deliver software products and services that enable our customers to cope easily and cost-effectively with changing business needs and operating environments.<br />
<br />
At UNIT4, we recognize that our employees are key to our success. We value them highly and take care to select the right kind of people to work with us. Do you have what it takes to help businesses embrace change? We look for UNIT4 team members who:<br />
&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>
have a <strong>CAN-DO ATTITUDE</strong>: Positive, self-starters who rise to the challenge and take personal responsibility for solutions and results</li>
<li>
have <strong>CUSTOMER EMPATHY</strong>: Delivering relevant value to customers by listening, understanding and reflecting back what is heard and providing solutions</li>
<li>
are <strong>HUMBLE</strong>: Respectfully collaborating in the best interest of the customer, company, team and self</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
UNIT4 Business Software is committed to a policy of equal employment opportunity.&nbsp; We recruit, employ, train, compensate, and promote without regard to race, color, age, sex, ancestry, marital status, religion, national origin, disability, sexual orientation, veteran status, present or past history of mental disability, genetic information or any other classification protected by state or federal law.</p>
