			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Do you have a keen eye for detail? Do you always notice the imperfections where ever you go?<br />
<br />
Are you passionate about the quality of products delivered to Customers?<br />
<br />
If you answered yes to any of these you may be the person we are looking for.<br />
<br />
<strong>Company Overview</strong><br />
<br />
UNIT4 Business Software is the North American subsidiary of UNIT4, a $550 million global cloud-focused business software and services company. It offers solutions that help Businesses Living IN Change (BLINC)&trade; in public, private, non-profit and higher education organizations embrace business change simply, quickly and cost-effectively. Agresso Business World, the company&rsquo;s flagship Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) suite and Coda Financials, its best-of-class financial management software, are used by 5500+ organizations in more than 100 countries. For more information visit www.unit4.com/na or follow the company on Twitter and LinkedIn.<br />
<br />
We have cultivated a challenging yet relaxed work atmosphere where people can get satisfaction from both doing great work under good conditions and from working with good colleagues, satisfied customers, while maintaining a healthy work/life balance.<br />
<br />
The Victoria UNIT4 Development team carries out a wide variety of software development activities: the development of two major and several minor products within the Agresso product suite; the customization of the product suite for specific customers, at scales ranging from very small to enormous multi-year projects; and the adaptation of the standard product to US and Canadian requirements.<br />
<br />
<strong>Job Summary</strong><br />
<br />
An Application QC Analyst is responsible for the quality of our products; the ideal candidate is passionate about software testing and has made this their chosen profession. You will be comfortable working alone and as part of a team with minimal supervision, be customer-focused, have a can-do attitude, excellent organizational skills and the ability to multi-task and work under pressure.<br />
<br />
<strong>Role and responsibilities:</strong><br />
&bull;Responsible for designing and executing tests cases to uncover defects and improve the overall quality of our software<br />
&bull;Reviewing requirements and providing feedback<br />
&bull;Test individual system components: web application, databases, APIs, utilities<br />
&bull;Triage and prioritize defects<br />
&bull;Plan and build effective test environments with useful test data<br />
&bull;Contribute ideas and suggestions to support the QC Team goal of continuous improvement<br />
&bull;Participate in shared learning with other team members<br />
&bull;Help to ensure that development project plans are achieved<br />
<br />
<strong>Experience/Skills Required:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Attention to detail, reliability, creativity and curiosity are key qualities for this role</li>
<li>
Knowledge of test practices and methodologies</li>
<li>
Required communication skills: providing feedback to developers, assertiveness to stand up for quality, communicating with customers</li>
<li>
Experience using&nbsp; Agile and/or structured SDLC processes</li>
<li>
Experience in Windows environments</li>
<li>
Show persistence and look for alternatives when facing road blocks</li>
<li>
Have a commitment to meeting deadlines</li>
<li>
Ability to estimate tasks</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Desirable Skills:</strong><br />
&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>
Familiar with business processes in a variety of sectors, in particular: Finance/accounting, Logistics, HR, Payroll, Student Information Systems, Travel or Project Management.</li>
<li>
Experience with SQL and Oracle databases</li>
<li>
Experience with Microsoft Team Foundation</li>
<li>
Degree or Diploma in Computer Science or related discipline or equivalent work experience</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>The lay of the land</strong></p>
<p>
The Software Developer reports to the Development Manager. He or she works out of the Victoria, B.C. office, has no direct reports and has minimal travel requirements.</p>
<p>
<strong>Join us in &ldquo;embracing change&rdquo;</strong></p>
<p>
Around the world, we look for potential employees who are confident team players and have an unswerving commitment to excellence in customer service to help us in our mission to deliver software products and services that enable our customers to cope easily and cost-effectively with changing business needs and operating environments.</p>
<p>
At UNIT4, we recognize that our employees are key to our success. We value them highly and take care to select the right kind of people to work with us. Do you have what it takes to help businesses embrace change? We look for UNIT4 team members who:</p>
<p>
